    "body": "@golkir @fvictorio \r\nAfter quickly converting my test script to TS, I noticed that the error is a result from `hre` not being globally available. \r\n\r\nThe fix for me was just importing `hre` from hardhat:\r\n```typescript\r\nimport hre from 'hardhat'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen, you can impersonate an account like so (ignore the red underline under `before`, since these test statements still compile as they should):\r\n<img width=\"782\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-01-17 at 12 09 53 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37757724/104851824-e9878200-58bc-11eb-84a6-efebc65a7e51.png\">\r\n\r\nHowever, you'll have to covert all calls to `ethers.ETHERS_METHOD` to `hre.ethers.ETHERS_METHOD`, yet this did solve the issue for me. Let me know if this does or doesn't solve the issue for you.",
